    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-30T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="280"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/2047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hinkle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Trujillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-30T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 30, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. For Moffat<note n="40" xml:id="d280fn40">Jay Pierrepont Moffat, Chief of the
                        Division of European Affairs.</note> from Pell. Rosenberg is telegraphing
                    the President reporting the successful results of the negotiation here which
                    have <pb facs="0221" n="212" xml:id="pg_212"/> far exceeded all expectations and
                    include a pledge on the part of the Generalissimo that existing general
                    legislation discriminating against Jews will be repealed. It would be of
                    invaluable assistance to Rosenberg and his associates in their dealings with the
                    Generalissimo from this point on if acknowledgment could be made of this
                    message. [Pell.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hinkle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
